All of these operations extend to sheaves of modules over a sheaf of rings formula_272; the above is the special case when formula_272 is the constant sheaf formula_274.

=== Basic functoriality ===
Since the data of a (pre-)sheaf depends on the open subsets of the base space, sheaves on different topological spaces are unrelated to each other in the sense that there are no morphisms between them. However, given a continuous map formula_275 between two topological spaces, pushforward and pullback relate sheaves on formula_1 to those on formula_277 and vice versa.

====Direct image====
The pushforward (also known as direct image) of a sheaf formula_10 on formula_1 is the sheaf defined by
