This function is known as a super-Gaussian function and is often used for Gaussian beam formulation. This function may also be expressed in terms of the full width at half maximum (FWHM), represented by :
formula_48

In a two-dimensional formulation, a Gaussian function along formula_49 and formula_50 can be combined with potentially different formula_51 and formula_52 to form a rectangular Gaussian distribution:
